        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &quot;Gujarat Pre-Matric Scholarship Scheme for Standard 1st to 10th&quot; by the Tribal Development Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to provide financial assistance for educational development to Scheduled Tribe students studying in Classes 1st to 10th. Through this scheme, scholarships are annually provided to boys, girls, and extremely backward students from Classes 1st to 10th.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "The scheme provides financial assistance in the form of scholarships. The amounts are as follows:\n> **For Boys**\n\n\n- Class 1 to Class 8: Annual scholarship of ₹750/-.\n\n\n- Class 9 to Class 10: Annual scholarship of ₹1,000/-.\n\n> **For Girls**\n\n\n- Class 1 to Class 5: Annual scholarship of ₹750/-.\n- Class 6 to Class 10: Annual scholarship of ₹1,000/-.\n\n> **For Extremely Backwards Students**\n\n\n- Class 1 to Class 8: Annual scholarship of ₹1,000/-.\n- Class 9 to Class 10: Annual scholarship of ₹1,500/-.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Mode of Disbursement:****** The benefits to the beneficiaries will be disbursed through the Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT) method. \n\n> **Frequency of Disbursement:****** The scholarship is provided annually.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide financial assistance for educational development to Scheduled Tribe students studying in Classes 1 to 10. Through this scheme, scholarships are annual",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
